This year marks the 10th anniversary of the Belt and Road Initiative (#BRI). Apart from grand signature projects, "small but beautiful" sustainable projects have been bringing new impetus to reshape the lifestyle and well-being of BRI-participating countries over the past 10 years.

The Port Vila City Community Sports Complex in #Vanuatu is the very example of a “small but beautiful” project. In response to the Agathis community, #Foshan city of south #China's #Guangdong province funded the Sports Complex as an outcome of the sister-city relationship with Port Vila.

In this episode, GDToday reporter, joining hands with Vanuatu Broadcasting and Television Corporation (@NewsroomVbtc), explores what the Sports Complex means to local residents and how a Chinese company @CCECC8 has integrated itself into the local society.
